"use strict";(globalThis.webpackChunkjonathanmintz=globalThis.webpackChunkjonathanmintz||[]).push([[364],{2251(e){e.exports=JSON.parse('{"archive":{"blogPosts":[{"id":"/2026/01/03/habit-change-12-years","metadata":{"permalink":"/jonathanmintz/en/blog/2026/01/03/habit-change-12-years","source":"@site/blog/2026-01-03-habit-change-12-years.md","title":"How I Started Changing Habits 12 Years Ago \u2014 and What I Learned Along the Way","description":"A decade of small choices that reshaped my health from the inside out.","date":"2026-01-03T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"Nutrition","permalink":"/jonathanmintz/en/blog/tags/nutrition","description":"Fuel quality, timing, and micronutrient support."},{"inline":false,"label":"Longevity","permalink":"/jonathanmintz/en/blog/tags/longevity","description":"Long-game strategies for healthspan."}],"readingTime":1.41,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Jonathan Mintz","title":"Biohacking Coach","url":"/","imageURL":"/jonathanmintz/en/img/jonathanmintz.png","key":"jonathan","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"title":"How I Started Changing Habits 12 Years Ago \u2014 and What I Learned Along the Way","authors":["jonathan"],"tags":["nutrition","longevity"],"description":"A decade of small choices that reshaped my health from the inside out."},"unlisted":false,"nextItem":{"title":"Light, Sleep, and Recovery Rituals","permalink":"/jonathanmintz/en/blog/2025/12/27/light-sleep-recovery"}},"content":"About 12 years ago I began a process that didn\u2019t look dramatic from the outside, but changed my life from the inside.\\nIt wasn\u2019t one \u201cmoment of awakening,\u201d but a series of small, consistent decisions that kept adding up.\\nI realized something simple:\\nI didn\u2019t lack information \u2014 I lacked daily practice.\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## The first things that left\\nGradually, not all at once, I removed:\\n- \ud83d\udead Cigarettes\\n- \ud83c\udf6d Processed sugar\\n- \ud83c\udf54 Processed food\\n- \ud83c\udf3f Cannabis\\n\\nNot out of struggle, but out of listening.\\nI noticed how my body responded, how my energy shifted, how my mind cleared.\\n\\n## Healing that didn\u2019t come from a pill\\nOver the years I dealt with:\\n- Recurring sports injuries\\n- Hormonal imbalance\\n- Fatigue that wouldn\u2019t go away\\n\\nInstead of chasing a quick fix, I started asking:\\nHow do I sleep?\\nHow do I eat?\\nHow do I train?\\nHow do I recover?\\n\\nThrough smart movement, simple nutrition, reducing unnecessary load, and listening to my body \u2014 real healing began.\\nNot magic. A process.\\n\\n## The current station: alcohol\\nIn recent years another step was added to the journey \u2014 a gradual reduction of alcohol.\\nThe deeper I learn, the clearer it becomes that even small amounts of alcohol:\\n- Disrupt the gut microbiome\\n- Affect white matter in the brain\\n- Load the liver\\n- Impact recovery, sleep, and overall balance\\n\\nI\u2019m not saying I\u2019ll never drink wine.\\nI do enjoy wine.\\nBut today the choice is conscious, minimal, and not automatic.\\n\\n## What really changed?\\nThe biggest thing I learned is this:\\nReal change doesn\u2019t start with what you stop \u2014\\nit starts with what you build in its place.\\n\\nMore presence.\\nMore connection to the body.\\nMore honesty with yourself.\\n\\nAnd it\u2019s a process.\\nEven after 12 years \u2014 it\u2019s still ongoing."},{"id":"/2025/12/27/light-sleep-recovery","metadata":{"permalink":"/jonathanmintz/en/blog/2025/12/27/light-sleep-recovery","source":"@site/blog/2025-12-27-light-sleep-recovery.md","title":"Light, Sleep, and Recovery Rituals","description":"Small light habits that deepen sleep and improve recovery.","date":"2025-12-27T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"Sleep & Recovery","permalink":"/jonathanmintz/en/blog/tags/sleep","description":"Circadian alignment, deep sleep, and recovery rituals."},{"inline":false,"label":"Biohacking","permalink":"/jonathanmintz/en/blog/tags/biohacking","description":"Practical experiments for long, healthy living."}],"readingTime":0.4,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Jonathan Mintz","title":"Biohacking Coach","url":"/","imageURL":"/jonathanmintz/en/img/jonathanmintz.png","key":"jonathan","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"title":"Light, Sleep, and Recovery Rituals","authors":["jonathan"],"tags":["sleep","biohacking"],"description":"Small light habits that deepen sleep and improve recovery."},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"How I Started Changing Habits 12 Years Ago \u2014 and What I Learned Along the Way","permalink":"/jonathanmintz/en/blog/2026/01/03/habit-change-12-years"},"nextItem":{"title":"Training for the Long Game: Strength + Aerobic Base","permalink":"/jonathanmintz/en/blog/2025/12/20/training-long-game"}},"content":"Your sleep system is light-driven. When light is right, hormones follow.\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Morning\\n- 5\u201310 minutes of outdoor light within an hour of waking.\\n- Keep caffeine for after your first light exposure.\\n\\n## Evening\\n- Dim overhead lights 2 hours before bed.\\n- Use warm lamps and avoid bright screens.\\n\\n## Night\\n- Keep the room cool and dark.\\n- If you wake, use low red light only.\\n\\nIf you want help dialing this in, I can build a simple light map for your home."},{"id":"/2025/12/20/training-long-game","metadata":{"permalink":"/jonathanmintz/en/blog/2025/12/20/training-long-game","source":"@site/blog/2025-12-20-training-long-game.md","title":"Training for the Long Game: Strength + Aerobic Base","description":"Build a body that lasts by pairing strength with easy aerobic work.","date":"2025-12-20T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"Movement","permalink":"/jonathanmintz/en/blog/tags/movement","description":"Strength, aerobic base, mobility, and sport."},{"inline":false,"label":"Longevity","permalink":"/jonathanmintz/en/blog/tags/longevity","description":"Long-game strategies for healthspan."}],"readingTime":0.36,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Jonathan Mintz","title":"Biohacking Coach","url":"/","imageURL":"/jonathanmintz/en/img/jonathanmintz.png","key":"jonathan","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"title":"Training for the Long Game: Strength + Aerobic Base","authors":["jonathan"],"tags":["movement","longevity"],"description":"Build a body that lasts by pairing strength with easy aerobic work."},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Light, Sleep, and Recovery Rituals","permalink":"/jonathanmintz/en/blog/2025/12/27/light-sleep-recovery"},"nextItem":{"title":"Fasting Rhythms: A 7-Day Cycle You Can Repeat","permalink":"/jonathanmintz/en/blog/2025/12/13/fasting-rhythms"}},"content":"Longevity training is not extreme training. It is repeatable, joint-friendly, and still powerful.\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Two anchors\\n1. **Strength:** 2\u20133 full-body sessions per week.\\n2. **Aerobic base:** 2\u20134 sessions of easy, nasal-breathing cardio.\\n\\n## What this builds\\n- Muscle as metabolic armor\\n- Mitochondrial density and stamina\\n- Faster recovery between life stressors\\n\\nIf you want a start, try two strength days and two 30-minute zone-2 sessions for three weeks."},{"id":"/2025/12/13/fasting-rhythms","metadata":{"permalink":"/jonathanmintz/en/blog/2025/12/13/fasting-rhythms","source":"@site/blog/2025-12-13-fasting-rhythms.md","title":"Fasting Rhythms: A 7-Day Cycle You Can Repeat","description":"A weekly template that balances metabolic flexibility with performance.","date":"2025-12-13T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"Fasting","permalink":"/jonathanmintz/en/blog/tags/fasting","description":"Time-restricted eating, fasting cycles, and refeed strategy."},{"inline":false,"label":"Nutrition","permalink":"/jonathanmintz/en/blog/tags/nutrition","description":"Fuel quality, timing, and micronutrient support."},{"inline":false,"label":"Longevity","permalink":"/jonathanmintz/en/blog/tags/longevity","description":"Long-game strategies for healthspan."}],"readingTime":0.53,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Jonathan Mintz","title":"Biohacking Coach","url":"/","imageURL":"/jonathanmintz/en/img/jonathanmintz.png","key":"jonathan","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"title":"Fasting Rhythms: A 7-Day Cycle You Can Repeat","authors":["jonathan"],"tags":["fasting","nutrition","longevity"],"description":"A weekly template that balances metabolic flexibility with performance."},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Training for the Long Game: Strength + Aerobic Base","permalink":"/jonathanmintz/en/blog/2025/12/20/training-long-game"},"nextItem":{"title":"The Biohacking Compass: Earth, Sun, Forest, Water","permalink":"/jonathanmintz/en/blog/2025/12/06/biohacking-compass"}},"content":"Fasting is a tool, not a religion. The goal is flexibility: the ability to burn fat, use glucose, and recover well.\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n### A simple weekly rhythm\\n- **Mon\u2013Thu:** 14\u201316 hour overnight fasts, protein-forward first meal.\\n- **Fri:** Early dinner, gentle 12-hour fast to protect sleep.\\n- **Sat:** Fuel for sport or training; no intentional fast.\\n- **Sun:** Optional 18\u201320 hour reset if energy and mood feel steady.\\n\\n### Notes\\n- Hydrate with minerals during longer fasts.\\n- Keep training intensity lower on longer fast days.\\n- Refeed with protein, fiber, and whole-food carbs.\\n\\nIf this feels good for two weeks, we can personalize with biomarkers and training load."},{"id":"/2025/12/06/biohacking-compass","metadata":{"permalink":"/jonathanmintz/en/blog/2025/12/06/biohacking-compass","source":"@site/blog/2025-12-06-biohacking-compass.md","title":"The Biohacking Compass: Earth, Sun, Forest, Water","description":"A simple framework to guide daily decisions for long, healthy living.","date":"2025-12-06T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"Biohacking","permalink":"/jonathanmintz/en/blog/tags/biohacking","description":"Practical experiments for long, healthy living."},{"inline":false,"label":"Longevity","permalink":"/jonathanmintz/en/blog/tags/longevity","description":"Long-game strategies for healthspan."},{"inline":false,"label":"Water","permalink":"/jonathanmintz/en/blog/tags/water","description":"Hydration, mineral balance, and cold water exposure."}],"readingTime":0.71,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Jonathan Mintz","title":"Biohacking Coach","url":"/","imageURL":"/jonathanmintz/en/img/jonathanmintz.png","key":"jonathan","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"title":"The Biohacking Compass: Earth, Sun, Forest, Water","authors":["jonathan"],"tags":["biohacking","longevity","water"],"image":"/img/jonathanmintz.png","description":"A simple framework to guide daily decisions for long, healthy living."},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Fasting Rhythms: A 7-Day Cycle You Can Repeat","permalink":"/jonathanmintz/en/blog/2025/12/13/fasting-rhythms"}},"content":"Biohacking works best when it is grounded. I use a simple compass that mirrors nature: earth, sun, forest, and water. Each element points to a daily practice that keeps health simple and sustainable.\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Earth: foundations\\nStrong sleep, consistent meals, and stable energy are the bedrock. If anything feels off, we reset here first.\\n\\n## Sun: timing\\nLight tells every cell in your body what time it is. Morning sunlight, evening dimming, and movement outdoors create effortless alignment.\\n\\n## Forest: adaptation\\nThe forest is diverse and resilient. We train the same way by rotating modalities: strength, aerobic base, mobility, and skill.\\n\\n## Water: recovery\\nHydration, minerals, breathwork, and cold exposure are the recovery river. When the water flows, stress drains.\\n\\nIf you want a simple start, pick one action from each element and repeat for a week. Your body will tell you what to keep."}]}}')}}]);